defaultI am writing to ask that Parliament considers including two clauses in the Deregulation Bill:
default&#xa0;
defaultMy wife and I have been keen walkers for many years and have been dismayed by the horrendous damage done by recreational vehicles (4x4s and motorbikes) in recent years to many green lanes. As the ruts become impassable even by these vehicles, they leave the green lanes and cause even more damage to surrounding land. The vehicles adversely affect wildlife and the noise they make is very intrusive for walkers looking for solace from the countryside.
default&#xa0;
defaultI  expressly
default support the formal submissions made by the Yorkshire Dales Green Lanes Alliance (YDGLA), by the Green Lanes Environmental Action Group (GLEAM), by the Green Lanes Protection Group (GLPG) and by the Peak District Green Lanes Alliance (PDGLA).
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
